node.text:
Take a classic for a spin this weekend.
.
Manhattans are truly one of the easiest cocktails to make. What sets them apart is the quality ingredients you use and how well they play together.
.
"Manhattan"
.
- 2 oz WhistlePig PiggyBack Rye Whiskey
- 1 oz Carpano Classico Vermouth
- 2 dashes Angostura Bitters
- Cherries for garnish
.
Add ingredients to a mixing glass, then add ice and stir until diluted.  Strain. Serve up in a in a Coupe or Manhattan Glass.  Garnish with some cocktail cherries and enjoy!
.
THEN PUT YOUR VERMOUTH IN THE FRIDGE!
.
🎥 - @bensation
.
.
.
#WhistlePig #PiggyBack #Rye #CarpanoClassico #PutYourVermouthInTheFridge

node.text:
Add a little fire to your #CincoDeMayo celebration this year. 🔥
.
Our #cocktailczar, @whistlepigla, needed a little inspiration this May 5th.  Luckily his friend and neighbor, @whistlepigsd, was ready with riff on a classic tradition.
.
"Rye-rita"
.
- 1 ½ oz WhistlePig PiggyBack Rye
- ¾ oz LOL Sour Mix*
- ½ oz Ancho Reyes
- 3 dashes Fee Bros Orange Bitters
- Lime Cup filled with 151 Rum

*LOL Sour Mix is equal parts fresh lime, lemon and orange juice with equal part 1x1 simple syrup.
.
🎥 - @bensation
.
.
.
#WhistlePig #PiggyBack #Rye

Tonight's forecast calls for clear skies and howling cocktails. 🌙
.
This riff on a classic "Americano" cocktail was inspired by @schecterguitarsofficial's Silver Mountain Blood Moon guitars.  The drink drips with delicious notes of blood orange and rye, the perfect sipper to be enjoyed by the light of a Blood Moon.
.
"The Blood Moon"
.
- 1 oz WhistlePig PiggyBack Rye
- 1 oz Galliano L'Apertivo
- 1 ¼ oz Starlino Vermouth
- 3 oz Runa Blood Orange
- 4 oz Topo Chico
- ¼ oz Liquid Cane Sugar
- 1 slice of Blood Orange for garnish
.
Add all ingredients to a glass. Garnish with a Blood Orange wheel. Enjoy!
.
🍹 - @whistlepigla
🎥 - @bensation
.
.
.
#WhistlePig #PiggyBack #Rye

We're celebrating #NationalCocktailDay with an ice cream-infused cocktail made with some of Vermont's best! 🍨
.
We're enjoying a cocktail made with new @benandjerrys Whiskey Biz Topped ice cream and WhistlePig PiggyBack Rye Whiskey.  Check out @benandjerrys page for a whiskey-infused cake and to pair with your cocktail for the full Green Mountain experience.
.
"The Closer"
.
- 2 oz WhistlePig PiggyBack Rye
- 3 oz Espresso
- 4 oz Milk based Dutch Hot Chocolate
- 1 tbsp WhistlePig Barrel-Aged Maple Syrup
- 1 healthy scoop of @benandjerrys Whiskey Biz Topper Ice Cream
- White Chocolate for Garnish
.
Add all ingredients to a coffee mug.  Garnish with with White Chocolate or use the White Chocolate Ganache from the pint.  Enjoy!
.
🍹 - @whistlepigla
🎥 - @bensation
.
.
.
#WhistlePig #PiggyBack #Rye

A simple cocktail that will steal the show. 🍸
.
Our #CocktailCzar (@whistlepigla) has been locked away in his libation laboratory creating simple yet powerful spirit experiments.  Equipped with a bottle (or six) of WhistlePig PiggyBack Rye he has developed easy-to-craft drinks ready for any day of the week. 🧪
.
"Starhattan"
.
- 2 oz WhistlePig PiggyBack Rye
- 1 oz @thestarlino Rosso Vermouth
- 2 dashes Angostura Bitters
- A few @thestarlino Maraschino Cherries for garnish
.
Add ingredients to a mixing glass, then add ice and stir till dilution.  Strain into a Coupe or Manhattan Glass and garnish with a Starlino Maraschino Cherry…or three! 🍒 
.
THEN PUT YOUR VERMOUTH IN THE FRIDGE!
.
#WhistlePig #PiggyBack #Rye #PutYourVermouthInTheFridge

node.text:
Power throuple.
.
The Maple Old Fashioned is a staple at the WhistlePig Farm and now we've made it effortless to create these classic cocktails at home.  A combination of PiggyBack 100% Rye, Barrel Aged Maple Syrup and Bitters (made in collaboration with our good friends over at @runamokmaple) you have an incredible cocktail suited for any time of year.  Check out the link in bio to find out more.
.
"Maple Old Fashioned"
.
- 2 oz WhistlePig PiggyBack 100% Rye Whiskey
- ¼ oz WhistlePig Barrel Aged Maple Syrup
- 3-5 dashes WhistlePig Barrel Aged Maple Bitters
- Fresh orange peel, to garnish
.
Add Bitters, Maple Syrup and PiggyBack 100% Rye to a rocks glass.  Add a large ice cube. Stir until chilled and Maple Syrup is fully dissolved into the cocktail.  Garnish with a fresh orange peel.  Enjoy!
.
.
.
